ule`, and `TopModule` must remain identical.\n*   The timing structure (`forever` clock, initial stimulus generation) must remain identical.\n*   The error counting logic must be translated into the queue mechanism, ensuring the *first* error time is captured.\n\n**4. Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\n1.  Use `logic` type for all wires and regs in the improved testbench, aligning with modern SystemVerilog practices and the golden testbench's use of `logic`.\n2.  Ensure queue indexing is correct when iterating to display the history.\n3.  The logic for queue management (`delete(0)` when size exceeds MAX_QUEUE_SIZE - 1) must be correctly implemented within the clock edge block.\n4.  The final status check must aggregate the total mismatches found in the queue history and identify the earliest time recorded.",
